On a relatively recent Ubuntu system you should be able to install and try out Kunquat by doing the following:

sudo -k apt-get install build-essential libwavpack-dev libpulse-dev python3 python3-pyside check libsndfile1-dev libsamplerate0-dev
./get_build_support.sh
./make.py
./make.py --prefix=~/kunquat install
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/kunquat/lib
export PYTHONPATH=`python3 -c "import os, sys; print(os.path.expanduser('~/kunquat/lib/python{0}.{1}/site-packages'.format(*sys.version_info)))"`
~/kunquat/bin/kunquat-tracker

NOTE: Kunquat is in an early development stage. Don't expect it to do anything useful.


On MacOS Sierra you should be able to install and try out Kunquat by doing the following:

brew tap cartr/qt4
brew tap-pin cartr/qt4
brew install wget pyenv libsndfile wavpack pkg-config check pulseaudio qt@4 cmake
pyenv install 3.4.3
eval "$(pyenv init -)"
pyenv shell 3.4.3
pip3 install pyside
./get_build_support.sh
./make.py --disable-threads --disable-tests
./make.py --disable-threads --disable-tests --prefix=~/kunquat install
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/kunquat/lib
export PYTHONPATH=~/kunquat/lib/python3.4/site-packages
~/kunquat/bin/kunquat-tracker
~/kunquat/bin/kunquat-player ~/kunquat/share/doc/kunquat/examples/example.kqt
